headline.main: WELLES PLEADS FOR FREE TRADE; Warns U.S. to Avoid Errors of Past -- Roosevelt, Churchill Stress World Peace Aims WELLES SEES KEY TO PEACE IN TRADE

lead_paragraph: President Roosevelt and Prime Minister Winston Churchill emphasized the importance of the future development of international trade as a foundation for a better world order, in messages read last night at the world trade dinner of the twenty-eighth National Foreign Trade Convention at the Hotel Pennsylvania.
